creditline: Gift of Mrs. C. C. Bovey
description: rug, Navajo, with a design of six broad bands in twill weave in red, yellow, black, orange, tan, and white central band of zigzag sawtooth bands with lozenges in the center; flanking it a band of stepped design in black and white; this is turn is edged with one band of stepped triangles at one end and two bands of the same design at the other; fringed at one end; unable to locate by Lisa Ranallo, Textile Department, 2/26/99
title: Rug
